  keywords={Cyclopaldic acid, Macrophomina phaseolina, Penicillium, Rhizoctonia solani, Sclerotinia sclerotiorum, antifungal agent, cyclopaldic acid, dimethyl sulfoxide, unclassified drug, Antarctica, antifungal activity, antimicrobial activity, Article, chromatography, controlled study, fractionation, fungal cell, fungal strain, fungistatic activity, growth inhibition, Macrophomina phaseolina, mass spectrometry, nonhuman, nuclear magnetic resonance, Penicillium, plant disease, reversed phase high performance liquid chromatography, reversed phase liquid chromatography, Rhizoctonia solani, Sclerotinia sclerotiorum, sediment},
