  keywords={Antarctic, Birds, Fungi, Ornithogenic soil, Pathogenicity, Amphotericin B, Animals, Antarctic Regions, Antifungal Agents, Fungi, Humans, Microbial Sensitivity Tests, Soil Microbiology, Temperature, Virulence Factors, Antarctica, South America, Aspergillus fumigatus, Aves, Fungi, Macronectes giganteus, Penicillium chrysogenum, Phalacrocorax atriceps, Pygoscelis antarcticus, Pygoscelis papua, Rhodotorula mucilaginosa, amphotericin B, antifungal agent, virulence factor, bird, climate change, concentration (composition), enzyme, enzyme activity, fungus, global climate, identification method, ornithology, pathogenicity, animal, Antarctica, fungus, growth, development and aging, human, isolation and purification, microbial sensitivity test, microbiology, pathogenicity, temperature},
